JSettlers is a web-based version of the board game Settlers of Catan written in Java. This client-server system supports multiple simultaneous games between people and computer-controlled opponents.

Initially created by Robert S Thomas as an AI research project. Now maintained by Jeremy Monin and the JSettlers team at http://nand.net/jsettlers/devel/ and github.
